Package com.cafean.client.analysis

Class ComponentStateEdit

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.undo.AbstractUndoableEdit
      • com.cafean.client.analysis.ComponentStateEdit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.undo.UndoableEdit
    public class ComponentStateEdit
extends javax.swing.undo.AbstractUndoableEdit
    This class creates an undoable edit for an AbstractComponent that does not store a direct reference to the component. This instead stores an ident reference to the component, an ident reference to the model, and a Category.

    • Method Detail

      • end

        public void end()
        This method should be called after all of the edits are completed. This stores the state of the modified component, and removes all of the keys in the two hashtables that have the same value.

      • setName

        public void setName​(java.lang.String name)
        Sets the presentation name for this edit, which will appear in the undo menu. The default is the label of the original component.
        Parameters:
        name - the String that will be used for the presentation name.
